Admin Secret

Description

A vulnerable company document portal with multiple security flaws.

Initial Observations

Users can register and log in

After login, users are redirected to /profile

Viewing page source reveals a JavaScript file:

<script src="/js/main.js"></script>

The script checks for an /admin link in the navigation bar to determine admin status.

Vulnerability: Mass Assignment

When registering, the server accepts extra parameters without validation.

Original request:

username=amr&password=amr

Modified request:

username=amr&password=amr&isAdmin=1

The backend does not restrict isAdmin, allowing privilege escalation.

Exploitation

Register with isAdmin=1

Login as the new user

Access /admin

Admin Functionality

The admin panel allows PDF generation from user input.

This functionality is vulnerable to SSRF.

Payload submitted:

<iframe src="http://localhost/flag"></iframe>

The generated PDF includes the response from the internal service.

Result

The downloaded PDF contains the flag.
